the ul, li, and a selectors are nested inside the nav selector

_partial.scss. The underscore lets Sass know that the file is only a partial file and that it should not be generated into a CSS file. Sass partials are used with the @import directive.

you have a couple of Sass files, _reset.scss and base.scss. We want to import _reset.scss into base.scss. @import 'reset'; in the base.scss file. When you import a file you don't need to include the file extension .scss. Sass is smart and will figure it out for you. When you generate the CSS you'll get:


